hpnicfDldp2.name: hpnicfDldp2

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hpnicfDldp2.description: Device Link Detection Protocol (DLDP) MIB. Device Link Detection Protocol is a private Layer 2 protocol, which can be used to detect and shut down unidirectional links (fiber or copper links) to avoid network problems.

hpnicfDldp2GlobalEnable.name: hpnicfDldp2GlobalEnable
hpnicfDldp2GlobalEnable.description: Enable(true) or disable(false) DLDP on the device.

hpnicfDldp2Interval.name: hpnicfDldp2Interval
hpnicfDldp2Interval.description: Indicates the advertisement packet sending interval.

hpnicfDldp2AuthMode.name: hpnicfDldp2AuthMode
hpnicfDldp2AuthMode.description: Indicates the authentication mode. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. none: not authenticated. simple: authenticated by a clear text password. md5: authenticated by MD5 digest.

hpnicfDldp2AuthPassword.name: hpnicfDldp2AuthPassword
hpnicfDldp2AuthPassword.description: Indicates the authentication password. Setting the password to a zero-length octet string means deleting the password. When read, it always returns a zero-length octet string.

hpnicfDldp2UniShutdown.name: hpnicfDldp2UniShutdown
hpnicfDldp2UniShutdown.description: Indicates the shutdown mode when a unidirectional link has been detected. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. auto: the port will be shutdown automatically. manual: the port must be shut down manually.

hpnicfDldp2PortConfigTable.name: hpnicfDldp2PortConfigTable
hpnicfDldp2PortConfigTable.description: This table contains all ports that support DLDP.

hpnicfDldp2PortConfigEntry.name: hpnicfDldp2PortConfigEntry
hpnicfDldp2PortConfigEntry.description: This entry describes a port that supports DLDP.

hpnicfDldp2PortEnable.name: hpnicfDldp2PortEnable
hpnicfDldp2PortEnable.description: Enable(true) or disable(false) DLDP on a port.

hpnicfDldp2PortStatusTable.name: hpnicfDldp2PortStatusTable
hpnicfDldp2PortStatusTable.description: This table contains all ports enabled with DLDP.

hpnicfDldp2PortStatusEntry.name: hpnicfDldp2PortStatusEntry
hpnicfDldp2PortStatusEntry.description: This entry describes a port enabled with DLDP.

hpnicfDldp2PortOperStatus.name: hpnicfDldp2PortOperStatus
hpnicfDldp2PortOperStatus.description: Indicates the DLDP operating status on the port. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. initial: DLDP is not globally enabled. inactive: physical status of the port is down. unidirectional: all neighbors of the port are in 'unconfirmed' status. bidirectional: more than one neighbor of the port is in 'confirmed' status.

hpnicfDldp2PortLinkStatus.name: hpnicfDldp2PortLinkStatus
hpnicfDldp2PortLinkStatus.description: Indicates the DLDP link status of the port. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. down: the DLDP link status of the port is down. up: the DLDP link status of the port is up. If the port operating status is not 'inactive', 'unidirectional', or 'bidirectional', it always returns 'unknown'.

hpnicfDldp2NeighborTable.name: hpnicfDldp2NeighborTable
hpnicfDldp2NeighborTable.description: This table contains all port's neighbors.

hpnicfDldp2NeighborEntry.name: hpnicfDldp2NeighborEntry
hpnicfDldp2NeighborEntry.description: This entry describes a port's neighbors.

hpnicfDldp2NeighborBridgeMac.name: hpnicfDldp2NeighborBridgeMac
hpnicfDldp2NeighborBridgeMac.description: Indicates the bridge MAC address of a neighbor.

hpnicfDldp2NeighborPortIndex.name: hpnicfDldp2NeighborPortIndex
hpnicfDldp2NeighborPortIndex.description: Indicates the port index of a neighbor.

hpnicfDldp2NeighborStatus.name: hpnicfDldp2NeighborStatus
hpnicfDldp2NeighborStatus.description: Indicates the status of a neighbor. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. unconfirmed: unidirectional communication between the port and its neighbor. confirmed: bidirectional communication between the port and its neighbor.

hpnicfDldp2NeighborAgingTime.name: hpnicfDldp2NeighborAgingTime
hpnicfDldp2NeighborAgingTime.description: Indicates the aging time of a neighbor. If the neighbor status is not 'confirmed', it always returns 0.

hpnicfDldp2TrapUniLink.name: hpnicfDldp2TrapUniLink
hpnicfDldp2TrapUniLink.description: This trap is generated when DLDP detects a unidirectional link, ifIndex and ifDescr identify the port.

hpnicfDldp2TrapBidLink.name: hpnicfDldp2TrapBidLink
hpnicfDldp2TrapBidLink.description: This trap is generated when DLDP detects a bidirectional link, ifIndex and ifDescr identify the port.
